Subject: Re: [T2] Mechanical Fuel Pump installation

On Friday, July 15, 2005, at 04:38PM, Shawn Luft <shawnagan(-at-)sympatico.ca> wrote:

>I am in the process of installing a replacement mechanical fuel pump.  In
>the Bentley is says to fill the lower part with universal grease.  Can
>someone please tell me if 'multipurpose wheelbearing & chassis lubricant' is
>a suitable replacement for universal grease ?  Will this work in my fuel
>pump?

Remember that some of the grease in that area is going to partly dissolve from contact with the oil that runs from the cam to the hole in the case before the pump:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Parts72Bus1/04-FuelPumpPushrod.jpg

So, either use a thick grease sparingly or a thinner one.

